title: This CEO is working to make a critical test for women's health more accessible: 'Even if the visit's free,' there are other barriers, she says
summary: The rate of cervical cancer screenings fell during the Covid-19 pandemic, and haven't rebounded. Teal Health created the first FDA-approved, at-home screening.

title: If you regularly react this way, you probably look insecure to others, says psychology expert—here's what to do instead
summary: You've likely heard of the fight, flight and freeze responses. But there is also a fourth, lesser known one: fawn. It can make you feel insecure, and make it harder to set healthy boundaries. Psychotherapist Meg Josephson shares some tips about how to handle it.

title: CDC takes down more than a dozen webpages on sexual and gender identity, health equity
summary: Some health equity advocates say removing such resources could create gaps in access to critical health information, especially for marginalized groups.
